<TITLE> Romanian banned refs to officiate internationals </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 BUCHAREST, Aug 2 (bdnews24.com/Reuters)- Two referees banned by Romania for performing badly during the opening league weekend will take charge of two international matches this month. Sebastian Coltescu and Augustus Contantin were banned for an undetermined period on Wednesday for making what the country's soccer federation said were "major errors" favourable to Bucharest clubs Steaua and Rapid, who both won their opening matches at the weekend. Coltescu takes charge of Armenian club MIKA Ashtarak's UEFA Cup match with MTK of Hungary on Thursday, while Constantin will oversee the Under-21 Euro qualifier between Croatia and Azerbaijan on Aug. 11
